           <div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_3 et_pb_column_2 et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough">
            <div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_1 et_clickable et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_center">
             <div class="et_pb_text_inner">
              <span style="color: #ffffff;">
               <a href="https://freeexpression.uchicago.edu/history/" style="color: #ffffff;">
                History
               </a>
              </span>
             </div>
            </div>
            <!-- .et_pb_text -->
            <div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_2 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_left">
             <div class="et_pb_text_inner">
              Through the Broyles Bills and McCarthyism, Vietnam protests and the Cold War, University leaders, faculty, students, and staff have defended and upheld the principles of free expression and academic freedom.
              <br/>
              <a href="https://freeexpression.uchicago.edu/history/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
               <strong>
                View the timeline
               </strong>
               .
              </a>
             </div>
