             <div class="et_pb_text_inner">
              <p>
               <span style="color: #ffffff;">
                <a href="https://freeexpression.uchicago.edu/files/2019/01/Free-Speech-Is-the-Basis-of-a-True-Education-WSJ-1v5hqit.pdf" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #ffffff;" target="_blank">
                 President’s Commentary
                </a>
               </span>
              </p>
             </div>
            </div>
            <!-- .et_pb_text -->
            <div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_4 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_left">
             <div class="et_pb_text_inner">
              <p>
               University President Robert J. Zimmer discusses the central importance of free expression to universities in a 2016 op-ed in the
               <em>
                Wall Street Journal
               </em>
               entitled “Free Speech Is the Basis of a True Education.”
               <br/>
               <a href="https://freeexpression.uchicago.edu/files/2019/01/Free-Speech-Is-the-Basis-of-a-True-Education-WSJ-1v5hqit.pdf" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
                <strong>
                 Read the article
                </strong>
                .
               </a>
              </p>
             </div>
            </div>
