             <div class="et_pb_text_inner">
              <p>
               <span style="color: #ffffff;">
                <a href="https://provost.uchicago.edu/sites/default/files/documents/reports/FOECommitteeReport.pdf" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #ffffff;" target="_blank">
                 Chicago Principles
                </a>
               </span>
              </p>
             </div>
            </div>
            <!-- .et_pb_text -->
            <div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_6 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_left">
             <div class="et_pb_text_inner">
              <p>
               In 2015, President Robert J. Zimmer and then-Provost Eric Isaacs appointed a committee of University faculty to articulate “the University’s overarching commitment to free, robust, and uninhibited debate.” The resulting “Chicago Principles” have since been
               <a href="https://www.thefire.org/chicago-statement-university-and-faculty-body-support/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
                adopted by universities and colleges across the country.
               </a>
               <br/>
               <a href="https://provost.uchicago.edu/sites/default/files/documents/reports/FOECommitteeReport.pdf" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
                <strong>
                 Learn more
                </strong>
                .
               </a>
              </p>
